       The rraanndd command outputs num pseudo-random bytes after
       seeding the random number generater once.  As in other
       ooppeennssssll command line tools, PRNG seeding uses the file
       $HOME/..rrnndd or ..rrnndd in addition to the files given in the
       --rraanndd option.  A new $HOME/..rrnndd or ..rrnndd file will be
